I have not drunk alcohol in years. I can't afford it. I have not been to a nightclub in years. I can't afford it.<br>
<br>
Quote<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Oh you want coke, I thought we were trying to save money here, its water ... its cheap.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
I can't afford to buy coke. I drink water and tea. I do drink coffee, which is probably the most expensive thing that I buy, and my stomach always lurches at the price.<br>
<br>
Quote<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>You hate tap water do you, well get a filter, they are very cheap if you don't buy the first one you see.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
Actually, I just drink tap water. Some people think its unsafe but I believe the government. It's safe. It tastes like horse piss, but its safe.<br>
<br>
Quote<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Oh you have to have name brand stuff huh? Guess what? Wal-Mart clothes are fine. You don't have to wear Nikes.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
8 years ago, I bought a pair of shoes. I'm still wearing the same pair of shoes. They are black, ordinary shoes. Not designer. No label. Just shoes. And they have holes in the soles. At the same time I bought the shoes, I bought a suit. It is my only suit. I still have it. When I left home for university, I bought a coat to treat myself. Two years ago, someone walked off with my coat in a nightclub, leaving behind their own. The two coats were identical except mine was small and his was large. I was unable to recover my coat. Ever since, I have been wearing a coat which is about 4 inches long at the sleeves. Yes I look stupid in it, but that's okay because I can't afford to go out anywhere anyway.<br>
<br>
Quote<br>
As for food there is plenty of food that is cheaper because its not &quot;name&quot; brand. <br>
<br>
I don't buy name brand food. Actually, I don't buy much food. I eat one meal a day. A year ago I was so thin that the doctor threatened to hospitalise me. Instead, I went to stay with my dad for a while, and he fed me up.<br>
<br>
Quote<br>
I am happy some one has let you use their computer and internet connection to post here<br>
<br>
Actually, I bought unmetered access for my computer. It's only at nights and at weekends, but its cheaper than buying a newspaper everyday and it's my only connection with the outside world. I don't have a tv. can't afford it. About a year ago my mouse broke. A few months ago my cdrom broke. About a month ago my monitor broke. My father bought me a new cdrom for my birthday. I am borrowing my brother's monitor and mouse.<br>
<br>
At the moment, I am in my dad's house. Unfortunately, there's been a hold up with my housing benefit. It meant I couldn't pay my rent. I had been using my inheritence to pay the rent whilst they sorted it out but it has run out. I have had ot move out of the shared flat I was in.<br>
<br>
This is all with the help of the state and with the help of my family. Without my family, I would probably be homeless by now. A lot of people don't have families like I do. Without the state, I wouldn't stand a chance.<br>
