<br>
Beeing single and high wages I pay around 42% taxes on my wage and on top of that there more taxes from the city and provence you life in for services they provide.<br>
<br>
We pay taxes for driving a car and pay high taxes on cigarretes and fuel.<br>
<br>
Companies who hire me pay a very high amount on top of the wage they pay me. It used to be for every cent you pay your employe you pay a cent to the goverment. I don't know how much it is now since there been some tax cuts in the past lowering the cost to hire somebody.<br>
<br>
The chances that I will become filty rich from all these taxes are probably slim but I got a 2nd chance and those around me have to. <br>
<br>
I would be a very happy man if they reduced taxes or atleast made our tax system more transparent and remove the double and tripple taxation but not at the cost of basic solidarity.<br>
<br>
We pay alot but we get alot in return from it but there is always room for improvement.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=drusila>Drusila</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/themes/blueMoon/unread.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/22/03 9:35:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=345.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Being Rich?!?</span><hr size=1> My earlyer point was not to whine about my own situation although I do see it as easly confused with that..<br>
<br>
I used my own situation when I know several other peoples stories that I could have used insted, I just feel that its rude to go speeking about someone else and much easier to speek about myself.<br>
<br>
It was to make the point that things we choose are not always the problem. I Chose a husband with a good reliable job, Medical insurance, life insurance Ect Ect.. We never chose for him to lose the ability to work and with it the health and life insurance.<br>
<br>
We did chose to care for his aging mother, because of the way things have happened in her life (and not all of them were chosen) she has almost nothing and if it were not for us she would have no one. I say it was a choice and Im sure it was but also it is an obligation IMO.<br>
<br>
It is frightening to know that if my son needs lifesaving medications or surgury he can not have it. <br>
<br>
If I am diagnosed with cancer I will have to die because there is no way I could afford a doctor.<br>
<br>
In either case explaining this to a child would be most dificult.<br>
<br>
You may sight darwin on this one.. maybe my son or I dont deserve to live because we are not wealthy enough or because we have made &quot;bad choices&quot; in some peoples estimation.<br>
